{"word":"H2187 - זָנַק - zânaq - zaw-nak' - Leap","slug":"H2187","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">זָנַק</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>zânaq"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>zaw-nak'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Leap"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D6;&#x05E0;&#x05E7; - za&#x0302;naq</b> - <i>zaw-nak'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>draw together</i> the feet (as an animal about to dart upon its prey), that is, to <i>spring</i> forward: - leap."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2190\">H2190</a>"}]}